    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT,
        TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT BUSHING REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAMSHAFT BUSHING REMOVAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>WHEN SERVICING THE CAMSHAFT BUSHINGS, THE CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARING MUST BE REMOVED FROM THE
                    CRANKCASE TO AVOID DEBRIS CONTAMINATION.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the camshaft bushing remover and installer
                <emph type="bold">SE-2893</emph>
                to remove the camshaft bushings.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>SE-2893 includes:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Puller screw</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Expanding mandrel</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Puller screw extension</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Expanding collet</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Pulling nut</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Back-up nut</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Thrust bearing</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150525">5.25</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150525" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12086" filename="../figcg1/CG12086.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.25 Camshaft Bushing Remover and Installer SE-2893.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The four camshaft bushings have the same inside diameter, but the outside diameter and widths
                        of each bushing are different, as is the crankcase bore into which each bushing fits. Refer to
                        the chart below.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BECAUSE OF THE DIFFERENT SIZE OUTSIDE DIAMETERS OF THE BUSHINGS, THE ORDER OF REMOVAL IS
                        LIMITED AS FOLLOWS: REMOVE THE FRONT AND REAR BUSHINGS FIRST. THEN REMOVE THE TWO INTERMEDIATE
                        BUSHINGS THROUGH THE FRONT OF THE CRANKCASE.
                    </para>
                </note>
